1
00:00:02,610 --> 00:00:03,530
Thank you, Rob.

2
00:00:04,920 --> 00:00:10,360
As we get underway in the holiday season, we hear those wonderful carols and songs,

3
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:15,890
and we see the Southern California fake snow painted in the windows of stores.

4
00:00:16,570 --> 00:00:18,330
We just want it to be cold outside.

5
00:00:18,970 --> 00:00:20,810
And I have to confess, we had a party.

6
00:00:20,910 --> 00:00:25,550
Our Crown Ministry study got together for our first social last night, kind of a quasi-Christmas party.

7
00:00:25,550 --> 00:00:30,670
And it was so hot, we couldn't even light the fire to make it feel like we were having winter.

8
00:00:31,670 --> 00:00:34,910
But, you know, that's why we live here, folks, and it is a wonderful thing.

9
00:00:35,650 --> 00:00:37,690
Praise God for beautiful weather the past few days.

10
00:00:37,870 --> 00:00:40,150
Praise God that he's been good to us.

11
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:42,500
We continue that in Advent.

12
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:48,120
And from last year, we talked about fear and hope.

13
00:00:49,290 --> 00:00:53,250
We talked about how fear can paralyze us from doing what God wants us to do.

14
00:00:53,610 --> 00:00:57,230
We talked about how trust in the Lord is the opposite of fear.

15
00:00:57,750 --> 00:01:00,770
And that if we give ourselves over to trusting in the Lord,

16
00:01:01,940 --> 00:01:05,800
He wants to use us to make a powerful difference in the world around us.

17
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:11,980
You see, God wants to use you and me to cleanse the world,

18
00:01:12,780 --> 00:01:16,020
to cleanse our culture, to make the world a better place

19
00:01:16,020 --> 00:01:21,300
in which to have relationships with each other and primarily with God himself.

20
00:01:22,370 --> 00:01:25,910
He wants to use you to bring the gospel, the good news of Jesus Christ,

21
00:01:25,910 --> 00:01:28,550
to others in your sphere of influence.

22
00:01:29,620 --> 00:01:30,840
And instead of holding back,

23
00:01:31,610 --> 00:01:33,630
instead of holding back in fear

24
00:01:33,630 --> 00:01:35,230
and living safe and secure

25
00:01:35,230 --> 00:01:37,950
and yet in some ways kind of banal lives,

26
00:01:37,950 --> 00:01:40,190
the opposite is to enter this world

27
00:01:40,190 --> 00:01:41,990
and to live with a godly confidence

28
00:01:41,990 --> 00:01:44,050
and to boldly go forward

29
00:01:44,050 --> 00:01:46,310
and make a difference for Him.

30
00:01:48,240 --> 00:01:50,120
You see, sometimes I think we Christians,

31
00:01:50,260 --> 00:01:52,080
we think the world is just plain evil

32
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:54,560
and that somehow what really matters in life

33
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:56,740
is spirituality and spirituality alone.

34
00:01:57,620 --> 00:01:59,820
But you know that that's been around a long time.

35
00:01:59,820 --> 00:02:03,540
That idea has been around since the time of the earliest Greek philosophers.

36
00:02:04,730 --> 00:02:05,570
It's not new.

37
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:08,970
Yes, the world is broken, the world is sick, and it's sinful.

38
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,520
But it's not inherently evil.

39
00:02:12,450 --> 00:02:14,230
You see, matter is not evil.

40
00:02:15,650 --> 00:02:17,230
Flesh is not evil.

41
00:02:17,310 --> 00:02:19,390
In fact, God created these things and declared them good.

42
00:02:19,970 --> 00:02:24,490
If you think about it, God is the one who took on flesh and redeemed it.

43
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:29,020
Made a difference in our world, in our souls.

44
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:33,230
And the church in the world has this challenge in front of it.

45
00:02:33,230 --> 00:02:37,410
It is easy sometimes for the church to want to hunker down

46
00:02:37,410 --> 00:02:40,170
and stay pure from the influences of the world.

47
00:02:40,550 --> 00:02:43,970
But Jesus, our Master, was one who came and entered the world,

48
00:02:44,860 --> 00:02:47,260
took on flesh, spent his life amongst people.

49
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:51,520
He was in the world, but as we've said, not of it.

50
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:54,670
And as his disciples, as ones who follow him,

51
00:02:54,970 --> 00:02:59,070
we are to enter the world with confidence because we have the Holy Spirit.

52
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:02,710
We have God with us in the form of the Holy Spirit.

53
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:07,850
And we're here to renounce fear and make a profound difference in the world around us.

54
00:03:08,350 --> 00:03:10,590
And so here we are at Advent, our second week.

55
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:14,410
And we're symbolically waiting for the birth of the Lord.

56
00:03:14,850 --> 00:03:21,390
And I'm encouraging us this way, to wait now for the return of the Lord.

57
00:03:21,510 --> 00:03:26,730
And in so doing, by serving Him with diligence and without fear.

58
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:30,200
I want you to listen to what the Scriptures teach us today.

59
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:32,520
This is not a typical Advent text.

60
00:03:33,890 --> 00:03:35,130
It's time to do something different.

61
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:38,890
I've chosen one that's probably the most non-advent you could get,

62
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:40,390
but I think you'll see why I've chosen it.

63
00:03:40,610 --> 00:03:43,650
From Matthew 25, would you take a look with me?

64
00:03:44,150 --> 00:03:47,130
But when the Son of Man comes in his glory,

65
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,620
and all the angels with him,

66
00:03:50,580 --> 00:03:52,520
then he will sit upon his glorious throne,

67
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,120
and all the nations will be gathered in his presence,

68
00:03:55,120 --> 00:03:58,780
and he will separate them as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats.

69
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:01,820
He will place the sheep at his right hand and the goats at his left,

70
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,880
and the king will say to those on the right,

71
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:10,320
Come, you who are blessed by my Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.

72
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:13,080
For I was hungry, and you fed me.

73
00:04:13,460 --> 00:04:15,740
I was thirsty, and you gave me a drink.

74
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:19,200
I was a stranger, and you invited me into your home.

75
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,300
I was naked, and you gave me clothing.

76
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:23,140
I was sick, and you cared for me.

77
00:04:23,840 --> 00:04:26,520
I was in prison, and you visited me.

78
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,270
Then these righteous ones will reply,

79
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:32,590
Lord, when did we ever see you hungry and feed you?

80
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:35,090
Or thirsty and give you something to drink?

81
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:37,450
Or a stranger and show you hospitality?

82
00:04:38,010 --> 00:04:39,290
Or naked and give you clothing?

83
00:04:39,590 --> 00:04:43,110
When did we ever see you sick in prison and visit you?

84
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:44,670
And the king will tell them,

85
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:48,190
I assure you that when you did it to the least of these, my brothers and sisters,

86
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:50,890
you were doing it to me.

87
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:54,760
And the king will return to those on the left and say,

88
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:58,100
Away with you, you cursed ones, into the fire prepared for the devil and his demons.

89
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,260
for I was hungry and you didn't feed me.

90
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,800
I was thirsty and you didn't give me anything to drink.

91
00:05:02,880 --> 00:05:05,620
I was a stranger and you didn't invite me into your home.

92
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:07,620
I was naked and you gave me no clothing.

93
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:10,820
I was sick and in prison and you didn't visit me.

94
00:05:11,990 --> 00:05:12,670
And they will reply,

95
00:05:12,790 --> 00:05:14,990
Lord, when did we ever see you hungry or thirsty or naked

96
00:05:14,990 --> 00:05:17,230
or a stranger in prison and not help you?

97
00:05:17,350 --> 00:05:18,030
And he will answer,

98
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:19,870
I assure you when you refuse to help

99
00:05:19,870 --> 00:05:21,730
the least of these, my brothers and sisters,

100
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:23,610
you're refusing to help me.

101
00:05:24,310 --> 00:05:25,850
They will go away to eternal punishment

102
00:05:25,850 --> 00:05:28,450
for the righteous will go into eternal life.

103
00:05:28,610 --> 00:05:33,120
There's a lot in this text, but I want to concentrate on this one idea.

104
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:41,720
When the disciples of Jesus serve fellow followers of Jesus, that Jesus is the one being served.

105
00:05:43,120 --> 00:05:48,700
Whatever we do to the least of these disciples, we do unto Jesus himself.

106
00:05:49,900 --> 00:05:51,840
There's a few things I want to point out from this text.

107
00:05:52,650 --> 00:05:58,370
The first one is that Jesus identifies himself with his disciples.

108
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:03,560
He so identifies himself literally with the disciples.

109
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:07,300
When you clothe a fellow believer, you are clothing Jesus.

110
00:06:08,180 --> 00:06:10,720
When you feed a fellow believer, you're feeding Jesus.

111
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,540
And on and on.

112
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,560
Jesus identifies himself with his followers.

113
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:23,720
And in that sense, the followers of Jesus truly are the hands and the feet of Jesus in the world today.

114
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:28,370
But as more than metaphorical application,

115
00:06:29,290 --> 00:06:31,970
An author, Leonard Sweet, opened me to some new ideas,

116
00:06:32,090 --> 00:06:35,330
and I did some research to validate some things I was reading,

117
00:06:35,390 --> 00:06:36,690
and I wanted to share them with you.

118
00:06:37,670 --> 00:06:38,330
These are fascinating.

119
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:41,410
I want to see that all truth is God's truth.

120
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:46,860
And sometimes the different sciences can inform our thinking in theology

121
00:06:46,860 --> 00:06:48,700
and about truth from God's Word.

122
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,280
And I want to share something with you I discovered.

123
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:56,060
In 1982, there were some laboratory experiments that were done by Alan Aspect,

124
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,600
building on a guy's work by the name of John Bell.

125
00:06:58,660 --> 00:07:08,640
And they showed that particles, this is so interesting to me, particles a few meters apart actually, in a sense, communicate with each other.

126
00:07:10,390 --> 00:07:11,810
And that sounds really bizarre.

127
00:07:12,130 --> 00:07:17,370
But you separate particles apart and they, in a sense, dance together even when they're separated.

128
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:22,620
And they began to think about, well, what does that mean if we can show this to be true in a laboratory?

129
00:07:22,620 --> 00:07:30,320
And it was said by John Gribben this, if everything that ever interacted in the Big Bang maintains its connection with everything it interacted with,

130
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:37,480
then every particle in every star and galaxy that we see knows about the existence of every other particle.

131
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:39,820
That's a wild idea.

132
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:44,460
Somehow, we're discovering that things are very interconnected.

133
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:48,560
Every particle has a connection with every other particle in the universe.

134
00:07:49,220 --> 00:07:51,700
Sharp and Walgate, two scientists, have said this.

135
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:58,940
The spooky, non-local correlations at a distance might evidence, listen, a holy ghost at work.

136
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:08,110
The scientists are patting the theologians on the back saying, that sounds like a god at work.

137
00:08:10,530 --> 00:08:11,710
They're catching up.

138
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:13,380
It's good news.

139
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:16,820
Think about this.

140
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:20,510
Things are connected.

141
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:24,080
We're showing that at the quantum level, things are connected.

142
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:28,160
So when you serve a fellow follower of Jesus, you're serving Jesus.

143
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:29,160
It's all connected.

144
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,900
Isn't that interesting how that begins to play out?

145
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,580
It's all connected.

146
00:08:34,860 --> 00:08:36,720
And here's the application of that.

147
00:08:37,160 --> 00:08:40,940
The practical outpouring of these ideas in this kind of mindset is this.

148
00:08:40,940 --> 00:08:46,940
The early church, when they began to serve each other and serve Jesus as they were all connected,

149
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:50,340
the early church exploded with growth.

150
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:54,140
It just mushroomed.

151
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:56,320
People loved each other.

152
00:08:56,320 --> 00:09:03,270
When the church learned to out-love the pagans, they out-served everybody.

153
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:09,410
And the early church were loving Jesus by serving their fellow pilgrims.

154
00:09:10,150 --> 00:09:12,920
When I love you, I'm loving the Lord.

155
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:16,320
When you love me, you're loving Jesus, because we're all connected.

156
00:09:17,220 --> 00:09:17,780
Isn't that amazing?

157
00:09:19,710 --> 00:09:23,210
See, the people in the time of the early church knew there was something radically different

158
00:09:23,210 --> 00:09:27,490
about those who called themselves the followers of what they called the way.

159
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:33,630
The people who followed Jesus had more love than the people who didn't.

160
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:38,990
People who followed Jesus had more ability to get out and do things

161
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:40,970
and make a difference in the community.

162
00:09:42,140 --> 00:09:45,060
There was a Holy Spirit tangible in these people.

163
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:50,220
And it came out in love in a phenomenal amount of different ways.

164
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:53,020
And the surrounding communities were saying,

165
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:56,320
we want what those people have.

166
00:09:57,020 --> 00:09:58,620
We want that kind of love.

167
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:02,640
We want something supernatural that's sweeping through those people.

168
00:10:04,380 --> 00:10:08,750
To the early church understood, when you serve others, you're serving Jesus

169
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:14,620
because they're connected, and the church grew by leaps and bounds.

170
00:10:15,980 --> 00:10:18,700
Friends, that can happen again today.

171
00:10:19,870 --> 00:10:21,650
I don't believe that was for then.

172
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:25,250
I believe that's then and the next day, all the way up to today,

173
00:10:25,390 --> 00:10:27,130
and all the way through tomorrow and the next.

174
00:10:27,370 --> 00:10:30,770
If we love people, love Jesus by loving other people,

175
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:33,740
the church, I believe, can explode again.

176
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:35,380
Are we ready to love?

177
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:36,820
We're ready to love.

178
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:39,540
The second thing I want to point out from this text

179
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:41,980
is when you love your neighbor as yourself,

180
00:10:42,540 --> 00:10:44,120
you are, in a sense, loving Jesus.

181
00:10:44,340 --> 00:10:45,500
Because by extension,

182
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,620
not only when you're loving people

183
00:10:47,620 --> 00:10:49,540
who are followers of Jesus

184
00:10:49,540 --> 00:10:50,500
are you loving the Lord,

185
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:51,840
but in the great commandment,

186
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:52,880
Jesus even said this,

187
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,420
you must love the Lord your God,

188
00:10:54,980 --> 00:10:55,760
all of your heart,

189
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,040
all of your soul,

190
00:10:57,340 --> 00:10:58,340
and all of your mind.

191
00:10:58,580 --> 00:11:01,100
That's the first and the greatest commandment.

192
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:06,680
And a second is equally important, to love your neighbor as yourself.

193
00:11:07,850 --> 00:11:09,950
When you're loving your neighbors, when you love your communities,

194
00:11:10,170 --> 00:11:15,290
when you love the people of your cities, by extension, you're loving Jesus as well.

195
00:11:15,290 --> 00:11:17,070
And I raise this question.

196
00:11:18,330 --> 00:11:22,930
Why is it today that schools and businesses and civic clubs

197
00:11:22,930 --> 00:11:26,870
are more known for loving the community than the churches?

198
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:32,370
Did you realize that nowadays in many schools and in many businesses today

199
00:11:32,370 --> 00:11:36,270
that public service in the form of getting out of the community

200
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:40,130
is mandated as part of what you do to be a part of that institution.

201
00:11:41,030 --> 00:11:42,070
It's just part of it.

202
00:11:42,290 --> 00:11:43,810
If you're going to work at a large company,

203
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:47,590
10% of your time must be placed back into the community.

204
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:51,200
The civic clubs are known for community service.

205
00:11:51,500 --> 00:11:54,580
The churches today are known for having closed-door meetings.

206
00:11:55,180 --> 00:11:57,690
It's not the way it's supposed to be.

207
00:11:59,600 --> 00:12:01,860
One of the challenges I've given to our staff here,

208
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:03,160
if you're on full-time with us,

209
00:12:03,160 --> 00:12:06,860
is that I want you to be mandated as part of your job description

210
00:12:06,860 --> 00:12:10,200
in some kind of civic organization in our community.

211
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:14,930
We've got to get back out there, not always in here.

212
00:12:19,210 --> 00:12:23,180
We've got to take seriously these words of Paul, Ephesians chapter 2.

213
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:27,720
For we are God's workmanship, created in Christ Jesus to do what?

214
00:12:27,880 --> 00:12:30,940
To do good works, which God prepared in advance for us to do.

215
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:34,320
The Living Bible does the same verse a little different way.

216
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,160
I want you to hear this.

217
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:39,720
It says, it is God himself who has made us what we are

218
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:42,100
and given us new lives from Christ Jesus.

219
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:46,480
And long ages ago, he planned that we should spend these lives, how?

220
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:49,940
In helping others in those good works,

221
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:53,300
in loving our communities, in loving each other,

222
00:12:53,460 --> 00:12:56,520
and by extension, by loving Jesus in so doing.

223
00:12:58,470 --> 00:13:00,850
I love what Martin Luther, the great church reformer, wrote this.

224
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:04,030
He says, no tree bears fruit for its own use.

225
00:13:04,870 --> 00:13:08,310
Everything in God's will gives itself.

226
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,300
Isn't that beautiful?

227
00:13:12,990 --> 00:13:17,570
One author in Contra Distinction pointed out this stark realism.

228
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:20,380
He said, something is terribly wrong

229
00:13:20,380 --> 00:13:23,620
when the strongest moral voice out there

230
00:13:23,620 --> 00:13:26,720
is Oprah Winfrey and Laura Schlesinger.

231
00:13:28,210 --> 00:13:29,090
Think about that.

232
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:32,130
I mean, they're saying some good things,

233
00:13:32,130 --> 00:13:35,050
but they're also saying some things that aren't so good.

234
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:38,300
It's time, friends, for the local church

235
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:42,800
to rise up, to serve, and to be counted.

236
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:47,150
It's time for local church to get out there

237
00:13:47,150 --> 00:13:50,590
and love this world by loving Jesus

238
00:13:50,590 --> 00:13:54,070
and loving these people and being obedient to Him.

239
00:13:54,450 --> 00:13:56,930
Love Jesus by loving our neighbors.

240
00:13:58,420 --> 00:14:00,460
It's time for the church to be known again

241
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:03,720
as the place where real love is manifested,

242
00:14:03,880 --> 00:14:06,600
where the communities are loved tangible ways,

243
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:08,640
where more than the service clubs,

244
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:16,750
the churches are known as loving communities that make a difference in the world. I'm not

245
00:14:16,750 --> 00:14:21,730
knocking the service groups. I think it's wonderful. But when people who may not know

246
00:14:21,730 --> 00:14:25,210
the Lord gather together and are known for loving the community more than the church,

247
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:29,910
church has a problem. It's time for us to get out and to love the world. And finally,

248
00:14:29,990 --> 00:14:36,710
I want to say this, that you individually, each of us, can make a difference. You can

249
00:14:36,710 --> 00:14:38,910
and do make a difference.

250
00:14:40,620 --> 00:14:42,380
Now, George Carlin said this,

251
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:43,760
a little wisdom from the comedian.

252
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:45,920
He said, scientists have announced today

253
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:47,860
they found a cure for apathy,

254
00:14:48,340 --> 00:14:49,980
but they claim that no one has shown

255
00:14:49,980 --> 00:14:51,180
the slightest bit of interest in it.

256
00:14:52,980 --> 00:14:53,480
It's true.

257
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:55,990
Contrary to that,

258
00:14:56,710 --> 00:14:58,510
the followers of Jesus are a people

259
00:14:58,510 --> 00:15:00,710
who know they were put on this earth

260
00:15:00,710 --> 00:15:03,510
for a purpose, for a relationship with God,

261
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:04,550
for each other,

262
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:05,530
and to do what?

263
00:15:05,570 --> 00:15:07,390
To make a difference in the world.

264
00:15:07,390 --> 00:15:11,630
We were placed here to make a mark for Jesus in the world.

265
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:13,310
It's the opposite of apathy.

266
00:15:13,670 --> 00:15:14,530
We have a mission.

267
00:15:14,810 --> 00:15:15,730
We've got a purpose.

268
00:15:16,090 --> 00:15:21,550
Can we embrace it, each of us, and as a church corporately, and go forth and serve?

269
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:27,680
As we're beginning to see with the challenge of the five coins that Pastor Dave has brought us into,

270
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:35,540
you can take five gold coins, five dollars, and make a big difference with something so small as a few coins.

271
00:15:38,590 --> 00:15:39,990
An encouraging word here,

272
00:15:40,980 --> 00:15:42,600
encouraging word there,

273
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:43,720
a hand over here,

274
00:15:43,840 --> 00:15:46,920
you can make a big difference in this world.

275
00:15:47,180 --> 00:15:48,420
Especially, think about it again,

276
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,220
if everything is connected,

277
00:15:51,170 --> 00:15:53,590
there's great power in loving somebody over here

278
00:15:53,590 --> 00:15:56,390
because you never know how that person's going to be awakened

279
00:15:56,390 --> 00:15:58,990
and transformed and do something over here

280
00:15:58,990 --> 00:16:00,110
and can change the world.

281
00:16:00,110 --> 00:16:01,450
And it starts with your hand.

282
00:16:02,340 --> 00:16:03,120
When things are connected,

283
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,960
loving a little bit can go a long ways.

284
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,340
It can make a difference in the world.

285
00:16:08,580 --> 00:16:11,510
It's the whole premise in the film, Pay It Forward.

286
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:14,210
A little bit can go a long ways.

287
00:16:17,030 --> 00:16:17,950
Think about that again.

288
00:16:18,980 --> 00:16:21,600
The smallest units of matter in science,

289
00:16:22,570 --> 00:16:26,510
packed into the quantum level at the most smallest level

290
00:16:26,510 --> 00:16:28,790
of the building blocks of the universe,

291
00:16:29,370 --> 00:16:33,410
are also the place where the greatest energy is released.

292
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:38,070
At the smallest levels, there's more energy than we know what to do with.

293
00:16:38,070 --> 00:16:43,150
The atomic explosion just shows what a small bit of matter can do.

294
00:16:43,490 --> 00:16:44,290
Now think about that.

295
00:16:44,350 --> 00:16:48,510
The smallest bit of love in the right places can do amazing things.

296
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:53,030
Small can make a big impact.

297
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,010
Leonard Sweet said it this way.

298
00:16:57,920 --> 00:17:03,520
As the figure skater spins faster, the smaller he or she becomes.

299
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:07,580
So the smallest units can amass the greatest amounts of energy

300
00:17:07,580 --> 00:17:11,560
and create the greatest amounts of change.

301
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,860
Never before has the world been so instantaneously reachable

302
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:18,920
by one person, one touch, one helping hand.

303
00:17:18,920 --> 00:17:22,300
If that doesn't fire up the salsa in your souls

304
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:24,120
to live lives of significance,

305
00:17:24,940 --> 00:17:26,520
he says, what will?

306
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:30,380
Does that just kind of make the salsa in your soul?

307
00:17:30,420 --> 00:17:31,380
I love that phrase.

308
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,240
Can somehow the reality that you can make a difference

309
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:36,020
with the smallest touch here and there

310
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:37,740
in the community loving people

311
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:38,960
because things are connected.

312
00:17:39,240 --> 00:17:41,620
Doesn't that make you want to get out and try something

313
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:44,400
and just watch how it extends in this world

314
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:47,560
instead of just staying in the walls of the church

315
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:49,820
to get out and change the world?

316
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:55,410
Millard Fuller was a millionaire entrepreneur,

317
00:17:57,330 --> 00:17:58,830
rich and miserable man.

318
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:03,200
He got to know some people who taught him Jesus,

319
00:18:04,940 --> 00:18:07,540
and he began a little organization called Habitat for Humanity

320
00:18:07,540 --> 00:18:09,260
to change the world.

321
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,080
Now homes are built all over the world

322
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:16,660
for those who do not have the means to purchase a fancy home.

323
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,540
He says, I don't do it this reason.

324
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:22,000
The reason I do what I do, and so many of our volunteers do what they do,

325
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:24,380
is because we're being obedient to Jesus.

326
00:18:25,630 --> 00:18:27,170
The organization started to change the world.

327
00:18:28,590 --> 00:18:32,070
Chuck Colson goes to prison for Watergate.

328
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:38,240
He's so burdened for the families of prisoners and prisoners like himself,

329
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:42,360
he starts a prison fellowship that now operates in 80 countries.

330
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:46,380
And from that, the Angel Tree Ministry delivers packages

331
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:50,460
and Christmas gifts to the children of those who are in prison.

332
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:52,900
It's starting out of an idea.

333
00:18:54,210 --> 00:18:55,430
It changes so many people.

334
00:18:56,940 --> 00:18:58,480
It's Bill McGee, a plastic surgeon,

335
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,100
who goes into third world countries

336
00:19:00,100 --> 00:19:04,530
to repair the cleft palates of children who were born with birth defects.

337
00:19:04,990 --> 00:19:06,010
They can't afford this.

338
00:19:06,710 --> 00:19:08,690
He goes around and makes a difference in every one of their lives,

339
00:19:08,690 --> 00:19:10,230
and they can point, why does he do it?

340
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:12,270
Because he's being obedient to Jesus.

341
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:16,690
Cheryl Maxwell and Pat Zollinger from this congregation

342
00:19:16,690 --> 00:19:20,510
give their time during the week

343
00:19:20,510 --> 00:19:23,750
to counsel and minister to those women

344
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:27,070
who have been abused in families and by their spouses,

345
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:28,730
and they minister to the children,

346
00:19:28,990 --> 00:19:31,550
and they give spiritual counsel and love

347
00:19:31,550 --> 00:19:34,950
and minister and touch to people right in this community,

348
00:19:35,170 --> 00:19:37,450
and they are changing lives

349
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:39,850
in being out there and loving people.

350
00:19:39,950 --> 00:19:41,990
They were acknowledged and honored recently

351
00:19:41,990 --> 00:19:43,250
by the Transitional Center

352
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:47,010
as two volunteers that they mentioned this church by name

353
00:19:47,010 --> 00:19:51,350
that are making a huge difference in the lives of people in this community.

354
00:19:51,430 --> 00:19:52,370
And I was so proud of them.

355
00:19:53,050 --> 00:19:53,990
So proud of them.

356
00:19:56,110 --> 00:19:58,750
I spent an evening this week with the Agape Circle for a little bit.

357
00:20:00,150 --> 00:20:01,390
And they told me, and we watched,

358
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:04,330
I saw how they put together and are taking things for White Cross

359
00:20:04,330 --> 00:20:07,610
and how they're sending those items across the globe

360
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:09,590
and actually going to some of our own missionaries,

361
00:20:09,690 --> 00:20:10,690
Mark Thompson in the Congo,

362
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:14,450
as he works in a hospital setting in the deep in the Congo

363
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:18,170
that is so far back, it seems almost primitive

364
00:20:18,170 --> 00:20:20,130
in terms of the medical science they have

365
00:20:20,130 --> 00:20:22,490
and the things, the bandages and the sheets

366
00:20:22,490 --> 00:20:24,130
and things that we tear and send and roll,

367
00:20:24,370 --> 00:20:26,310
that send out there, they use that stuff

368
00:20:26,310 --> 00:20:29,290
and it touches lives in the most amazing places.

369
00:20:30,650 --> 00:20:32,090
From some people gathered together,

370
00:20:32,790 --> 00:20:34,970
sharing fellowship and rolling bandages,

371
00:20:35,050 --> 00:20:37,970
so simple, but changing the world, touching lives.

372
00:20:38,290 --> 00:20:41,970
I can go on and on and on with stories like that.

373
00:20:42,170 --> 00:20:44,510
Friends, we can make a big difference in the community

374
00:20:44,510 --> 00:20:45,950
in the home of our friends and neighbors.

375
00:20:46,230 --> 00:20:48,750
We can make a difference right here in this church facility.

376
00:20:49,090 --> 00:20:51,410
But the question is, do we really believe that?

377
00:20:52,090 --> 00:20:54,690
Do we believe that our lives count for something

378
00:20:54,690 --> 00:20:56,890
to make a difference in this world?

379
00:20:57,950 --> 00:21:00,530
I hope I'm getting the salsa in your soul fired up.

380
00:21:00,910 --> 00:21:02,910
I hope the little chili peppers in your soul

381
00:21:02,910 --> 00:21:05,030
are starting to ignite and get warm.

382
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:06,050
And you're saying, you know,

383
00:21:06,730 --> 00:21:09,020
I'm going to get out there and do something.

384
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:11,250
Because I love my Lord Jesus.

385
00:21:12,220 --> 00:21:13,920
I want to love somebody in His name.

386
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:17,180
and you never know how this is connected to that,

387
00:21:17,500 --> 00:21:18,420
it's connected to this,

388
00:21:18,680 --> 00:21:21,220
how one bit of pouring into this person

389
00:21:21,220 --> 00:21:24,760
can have huge impact in our world.

390
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:28,100
How do you make a difference?

391
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:30,880
Let's talk about the church for a minute.

392
00:21:31,020 --> 00:21:32,240
Let's talk about people who come here.

393
00:21:32,580 --> 00:21:34,060
Let's be really honest for a second.

394
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:40,230
The day is gone when people kept their stuff indoors.

395
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:45,300
The day is gone when people wanted to come to a church

396
00:21:45,300 --> 00:21:46,580
and everybody had their act together.

397
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:50,340
Friends, people's stuff, their dysfunction, is just out there.

398
00:21:50,420 --> 00:21:52,360
It's on television. It's just part of talk show.

399
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:53,940
It's just the world we live in.

400
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,680
It's out there. There's no more secrets.

401
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,420
And the reality is this.

402
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:59,680
People want to come into the church and they want to know,

403
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:03,460
are other people here still trying to put things together,

404
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:05,360
or does everybody have their act together?

405
00:22:06,260 --> 00:22:06,800
Friends, we don't.

406
00:22:07,560 --> 00:22:08,460
We just pretend like we do.

407
00:22:09,810 --> 00:22:11,490
Can we be the place where people can come

408
00:22:11,490 --> 00:22:15,620
and not be insecure that everybody has their act together,

409
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:17,880
but the church is a place where they can get real needs met?

410
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:24,500
Well, they know that if they come, they can put their lives back together because Jesus is here.

411
00:22:27,140 --> 00:22:31,140
You see, we may not feel like we can do everything for everybody.

412
00:22:32,010 --> 00:22:33,530
And that's why there's lots of different kinds of churches.

413
00:22:33,610 --> 00:22:38,310
We really can't meet every single need that comes through, but we can meet a lot of needs as they come through.

414
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:40,200
And here's the basic thing.

415
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:45,280
We know these basic issues, and if we know these basic issues, we can touch the lives of other people.

416
00:22:45,520 --> 00:22:47,680
We can minister to others, and here's why.

417
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:52,740
Because we know that humanity is flawed and broken and sinful.

418
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:56,420
We know that people are seeking meaning to their lives,

419
00:22:57,180 --> 00:23:00,100
answers for their souls, healing for their hearts.

420
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:05,250
We know that Jesus came to fulfill those needs and to offer forgiveness

421
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:07,730
and to offer peace with God.

422
00:23:07,810 --> 00:23:08,910
We can tell somebody that.

423
00:23:10,130 --> 00:23:14,750
And if we know those basics, if we can just get a handle on those few basic issues,

424
00:23:14,970 --> 00:23:17,550
then we can simply listen to somebody else's story

425
00:23:17,550 --> 00:23:23,010
and we can find the links between their story and God's story.

426
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,740
We can find the links and make a few connections.

427
00:23:27,700 --> 00:23:28,760
We can all be ministers.

428
00:23:30,060 --> 00:23:32,830
We are all ministers.

429
00:23:35,240 --> 00:23:36,940
And if fear is holding us back,

430
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:39,920
we can release ourselves

431
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:42,700
and ask the power of the Holy Spirit to fill us,

432
00:23:43,750 --> 00:23:46,150
to free us from the fear of loving other people,

433
00:23:46,150 --> 00:23:49,130
from the fear of getting involved in the lives of people.

434
00:23:49,130 --> 00:23:53,730
we can, if we renounce fear, make a huge difference in this world.

435
00:23:55,610 --> 00:23:58,650
That's the kind of church that Jesus is calling us to be.

436
00:23:59,210 --> 00:24:01,510
It makes a huge difference in this community.

437
00:24:02,990 --> 00:24:10,110
Ken Miedema, an amazing musician, an amazing theologian in his own right,

438
00:24:11,040 --> 00:24:12,720
is the kind of man who is blind,

439
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:19,080
and yet because his lack of sight has developed his ear in a powerful way,

440
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:21,180
he's the guy that can sit and listen to a sermon,

441
00:24:21,180 --> 00:24:25,220
and by the end of the message, he'll go to the piano and play a song

442
00:24:25,220 --> 00:24:28,380
that encapsulates the entire heart of that message.

443
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,000
And he did it in about three minutes.

444
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:35,020
He wrote this after a message he heard.

445
00:24:35,970 --> 00:24:36,370
He wrote,

446
00:24:36,550 --> 00:24:41,590
If this is not the place where tears are understood, where can I go to cry?

447
00:24:44,210 --> 00:24:49,380
If this is not the place where my spirit can take wing, where do I go to fly?

448
00:24:50,970 --> 00:24:54,790
If this, the church, is not the place where my questions can be asked,

449
00:24:55,150 --> 00:24:57,350
Where do I go to seek?

450
00:24:58,580 --> 00:25:01,260
If this is not the place where my feelings can be heard,

451
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,340
where do I go to speak?

452
00:25:05,370 --> 00:25:08,170
If this is not the place where you accept me just as I am,

453
00:25:09,180 --> 00:25:10,480
where do I go to be free?

454
00:25:11,950 --> 00:25:16,430
If this is not the place where I can try and grow and love,

455
00:25:16,430 --> 00:25:20,190
where do I go to be just me?

456
00:25:21,740 --> 00:25:23,080
Great words for the church.

457
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,700
Friends, you are God's people,

458
00:25:27,580 --> 00:25:29,880
redeemed and loved and sanctified.

459
00:25:31,100 --> 00:25:34,740
Made ready and beautiful to serve and to love this world.

460
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:36,980
This is the body of Christ.

461
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:41,440
And if that kind of love doesn't pour out of the body of Christ,

462
00:25:41,580 --> 00:25:43,180
then where is it going to come from?

463
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:46,100
It must come from us as the people of God.

464
00:25:46,580 --> 00:25:47,980
Philip Yancey, you know I love his writing.

465
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:49,860
He said in a great quote here,

466
00:25:49,860 --> 00:25:51,560
he says, in a paradox of faith,

467
00:25:52,730 --> 00:25:56,890
the one who shares love comes away enriched, not impoverished.

468
00:25:57,490 --> 00:25:58,090
You notice that?

469
00:25:59,080 --> 00:26:00,800
That's why it's more blessed to give than to receive.

470
00:26:01,590 --> 00:26:04,490
Because in the act of giving, you actually are enriched.

471
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:07,360
In pouring out, you're filled.

472
00:26:08,310 --> 00:26:09,150
It's a great paradox.

473
00:26:09,590 --> 00:26:12,350
The more you take in Jesus, and then the more you give out,

474
00:26:12,350 --> 00:26:17,890
the more you're blessed, and you're the one that walks away truly filled and encouraged.

475
00:26:20,730 --> 00:26:24,990
When you love others, when you get involved, when you serve, you actually become enriched.

476
00:26:25,670 --> 00:26:27,290
The teacher walks away more blessed.

477
00:26:27,410 --> 00:26:29,750
The preacher actually learns the message better than anybody else.

478
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:33,320
The servant who gets involved in the lives of people

479
00:26:33,320 --> 00:26:36,660
actually walks away that night and sits down

480
00:26:36,660 --> 00:26:40,170
and is more blessed than actually the one who received.

481
00:26:43,030 --> 00:26:45,210
For those who do, you see they grow.

482
00:26:46,320 --> 00:26:47,680
When you get out and do these things,

483
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,780
you are enriched, your soul grows.

484
00:26:52,240 --> 00:26:52,700
That's good.

485
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:56,420
So last, I want to say, who is God calling you to minister to?

486
00:26:58,680 --> 00:27:02,720
Who in your life are you sensing that God really wants you

487
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:04,220
to make a difference in their life?

488
00:27:06,170 --> 00:27:09,980
Where can you get involved in the ministry?

489
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:13,720
Where can you be involved in what the Holy Spirit is doing?

490
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:18,660
Where is God calling you, each of us,

491
00:27:19,620 --> 00:27:21,760
corporately and individually, to make a difference?

492
00:27:22,710 --> 00:27:25,770
Where, as we wait for the return of the Lord,

493
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:29,100
are we called to make a difference?

494
00:27:31,060 --> 00:27:33,180
And I would ask what names and faces are coming to mind.

495
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:36,380
I suspect that there are people that God is placing in your mind

496
00:27:36,380 --> 00:27:39,740
that you know you're supposed to be out there loving in some way.

497
00:27:41,020 --> 00:27:41,660
It could be family.

498
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:43,440
It could be your neighbors.

499
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:44,640
It could be friends.

500
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:46,160
It could be somebody that you met here.

501
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:47,400
Who knows?

502
00:27:48,760 --> 00:27:50,260
But God wants to make a difference through you.

503
00:27:53,530 --> 00:27:55,810
By loving others, we love our Lord.

504
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:58,580
By loving others, we love Jesus.

505
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:03,200
Can we be the hands and feet of the Lord in this world today?

506
00:28:04,620 --> 00:28:07,360
We're waiting symbolically for the birth of the Son.

507
00:28:07,940 --> 00:28:09,900
We're really waiting for the return of the Lord.

508
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:14,540
And until he comes, we have a mission to make a difference in our world.

509
00:28:14,540 --> 00:28:20,320
And so while everybody is gathered to have the parties and to celebrate this season,

510
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:24,780
we can come and share and communicate the real reason for this season.

511
00:28:25,570 --> 00:28:27,210
And to love others in Jesus' name.

512
00:28:27,230 --> 00:28:30,310
And tell them, I'm doing this because I love Jesus and I want you to love him as well.

513
00:28:31,690 --> 00:28:33,010
And make a huge difference in the world.

514
00:28:34,260 --> 00:28:34,580
Let's pray.

515
00:28:34,700 --> 00:28:41,260
Father, help us to see that you've raised us up

516
00:28:41,260 --> 00:28:44,350
and given us gifts and talents in the Holy Spirit

517
00:28:44,350 --> 00:28:47,560
to make a huge difference in this world.

518
00:28:49,100 --> 00:28:50,660
So Father, may we renounce fear.

519
00:28:50,660 --> 00:28:52,060
may we put that aside

520
00:28:52,060 --> 00:28:55,020
and trust in your Holy Spirit

521
00:28:55,020 --> 00:28:56,860
to move boldly into this world

522
00:28:56,860 --> 00:29:00,830
to love you by loving others

523
00:29:00,830 --> 00:29:04,290
I pray that you'd open up doors

524
00:29:04,290 --> 00:29:05,610
and windows and outlets

525
00:29:05,610 --> 00:29:06,990
for expression of love

526
00:29:06,990 --> 00:29:09,050
that you'd put people in our lives

527
00:29:09,050 --> 00:29:10,050
directly in front of us

528
00:29:10,050 --> 00:29:11,130
that we can't step around

529
00:29:11,130 --> 00:29:13,510
that you're calling us to step out

530
00:29:13,510 --> 00:29:15,450
and make a difference

531
00:29:15,450 --> 00:29:17,460
and then by loving them

532
00:29:17,460 --> 00:29:17,980
we love you

533
00:29:17,980 --> 00:29:21,700
thank you that you came

534
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:22,620
and took on flesh

535
00:29:22,620 --> 00:29:26,270
now may we love people

536
00:29:26,270 --> 00:29:28,500
and touch them

537
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:29,900
and hold them and encourage them.

538
00:29:30,160 --> 00:29:32,240
Put a hand on their back and say Jesus loves them.

539
00:29:36,480 --> 00:29:38,000
Father, I pray you do great things

540
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,140
through Fullerton First Baptist.

541
00:29:41,140 --> 00:29:43,380
Father, you've called us here for over 100 years

542
00:29:43,380 --> 00:29:47,010
to shine the truth in this community.

543
00:29:48,100 --> 00:29:49,580
We're not about to roll over.

544
00:29:51,150 --> 00:29:53,370
Father, the fire is just growing bigger.

545
00:29:56,110 --> 00:29:57,250
I pray you give us that kind of vision,

546
00:29:58,700 --> 00:29:59,560
a heart for the community.

547
00:30:01,160 --> 00:30:03,000
I pray that our community would know

548
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,600
Fullerton First Baptist as a church that prays,

549
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:07,460
a church that plays,

550
00:30:07,460 --> 00:30:09,020
a church that loves

551
00:30:09,020 --> 00:30:10,840
and makes a huge difference

552
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:12,800
in North Orange County

553
00:30:12,800 --> 00:30:13,700
and beyond

554
00:30:13,700 --> 00:30:17,300
spark in us Lord

555
00:30:17,300 --> 00:30:20,040
a desire

556
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:21,540
a passion

557
00:30:21,540 --> 00:30:25,220
to love you in tangible ways

558
00:30:25,220 --> 00:30:27,200
this holiday season and beyond

559
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:30,040
and we're going to look forward to the fruit

560
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:31,260
you'll bring through that Lord

561
00:30:31,260 --> 00:30:34,210
so raise us up

562
00:30:34,210 --> 00:30:37,080
prepare us for the things you have for us

563
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:41,280
and we give you thanks

564
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:42,640
for the privilege

565
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:44,880
of being a part of what you're doing in the world

566
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:47,620
so Father we're going to sing

567
00:30:47,620 --> 00:30:49,820
these songs will come as we are.

568
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:51,620
Take us as we are.

569
00:30:51,880 --> 00:30:53,060
Use us as we are.

570
00:30:53,540 --> 00:30:55,670
Fill us up and send us out.

571
00:30:58,530 --> 00:31:00,250
And Lord, I pray now for those this morning

572
00:31:00,250 --> 00:31:03,820
who are sensing a call upon their life

573
00:31:03,820 --> 00:31:07,660
to commit to a new level of ministry

574
00:31:07,660 --> 00:31:10,440
or to give their lives to you for the first time.

575
00:31:11,750 --> 00:31:13,250
Father, you'd stir within them desire

576
00:31:13,250 --> 00:31:15,070
to take that step,

577
00:31:15,960 --> 00:31:18,120
to be counted, to be found.

578
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,360
Minister this morning, I pray, by your Holy Spirit.

579
00:31:23,120 --> 00:31:24,100
In Jesus' name.

580
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:54,260
Thank you.

